  <body>
    <header>
      <para style="margin-bottom:10px; line-height:2.0;"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">X_Prime</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">X_Prime</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> returns the X coordinate of a node or the element center in grid coordinates (fig. 19). &#160;(See </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="The_Grid" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The Grid</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">.) </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">For SUTRA models, &#160;</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">X_Prime</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is the same as </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="X" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">X</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> if it is used as in a default formula for a mesh. However, if it is used in a formula for an object drawn on the front view of the model, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">X_Prime</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is calculated using the angle of the cross section at the time the object was created. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><conditional-text type="IF" value="CHM,HLP,HXS,HTML,DEMO,USER1,USER2,USER3"/></para>
